1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:06,000
Architecture Governance Copilot is our Accelerate 3.0
proof of concept from Two Tokens One Brain.

2
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:11,700
It turns architecture work into an accountable,
evidence-backed governance record.

3
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:18,000
Product Owners and development teams prepare
the Solution Intent using a required template.

4
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:24,000
The official document remains in Confluence,
and an Azure DevOps ticket tracks the review.

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:30,000
A Domain Architect reviews it through Teams meetings
and revision rounds.

6
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:35,700
This proof of concept uses synthetic local content
representing those sources.

7
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:39,900
Those handoffs scatter decisions, risks,
actions, and evidence.

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,700
Teams then rebuild the governance record manually.

9
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:51,700
The Copilot drafts the SI, structures its review,
preserves evidence, and keeps humans in control.

10
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:57,700
Target architecture deploys the front end in Service Bench
and backend API in SKE.

11
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:03,700
Controlled adapters connect Confluence, Teams, AIF LLM,
database, and Azure DevOps.

12
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:09,700
The application opens at Draft Solution Intent,
the first of four visible stages.

13
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:14,900
Demo mode uses synthetic data, local processing,
and no external connections.

14
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:21,800
I load the SI template, selected source-code context,
and supporting notes for a fictional service.

15
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:28,700
Generate SI Draft validates that context
and creates an editable draft.

16
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:35,700
This is a drafting aid, not publication or approval.
I explicitly confirm the draft.

17
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:42,000
The application then moves to Review Inputs,
preserving the confirmed Solution Intent.

18
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:49,600
I add the matching Teams-style transcript
and review metadata, then select Analyze Review.

19
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:56,400
A separate Human Review page opens
with a Changes Requested outcome.

20
00:01:56,500 --> 00:02:03,500
The summary shows one decision, three findings,
one risk, two actions, and one open question,

21
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:07,500
plus two missing-information items.

22
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:13,000
The decision accepts managed PostgreSQL
as the system of record.

23
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:20,500
Findings identify missing traffic-failover behaviour,
missing RTO and RPO values,

24
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:26,000
and undefined production support ownership.
Database sizing is a release risk.

25
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:33,000
Each item retains a source quote from
the Solution Intent, transcript, or both.

26
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:37,000
This remains a proposal, not an approval.

27
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:43,800
The reviewer can inspect evidence, edit fields,
and include or exclude items.

28
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:50,400
I change the first action owner
to the synthetic value Taylor Kim,

29
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:56,000
then exclude the unresolved Redis question.
Evidence stays read-only.

30
00:02:56,100 --> 00:03:02,800
Only after human review do I confirm the record
and generate outputs.

31
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:09,300
The completed package preserves those choices:
Taylor Kim appears in the review record

32
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:14,600
and first Azure DevOps work-item preview,
while the Redis question is absent.

33
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:18,700
The output is preview-only;
nothing was submitted to Azure DevOps.

34
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:24,600
This workflow reduces manual review administration
and supports more consistent records.

35
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:29,500
It also improves evidence traceability.

36
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:34,700
Every record remains human-reviewed, and authority
stays with the Domain Architect.

37
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:39,000
Architecture Governance Copilot demonstrates
a practical, human-controlled path

38
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,700
from architecture context to accountable action.
Two Tokens One Brain.
